[
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Task.succeed</code> is a pretty long name to write out. What if we called it <code>Task.ok</code> instead? <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 341930724,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1678838824
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would that mean changing <a href=\"http://Task.fail\">Task.fail</a> to Task.err as well?</p>",
        "id": 341931241,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Hallstrom",
        "timestamp": 1678839117
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>that would make sense to me, sure <span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span></p>",
        "id": 341931403,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1678839206
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>now that we have <code>!</code> I'd like to revisit this</p>",
        "id": 440362307,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1716483058
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>we have the convention of always using <code>!</code> at the end of branches, which I like!</p>",
        "id": 440362382,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1716483084
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kr\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">Stdout</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">line</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"blah\"</span>\n<span class=\"kr\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">Stdout</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">line</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"something\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 440362422,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1716483100
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>however, it looks strange to me to follow this convention with <code>Task.ok</code> and <code>Task.err</code> <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span> </p>\n<p>e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">answer</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">Stdin</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">line</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">Task</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ok</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"something\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 440362652,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1716483183
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>Task.succeed!</code> and <code>Task.fail!</code> feel more natural to me compared to <code>Task.ok!</code> and <code>Task.err!</code></p>\n<p>however, it looks strange to me to follow this convention with <code>Task.ok</code> and <code>Task.err</code> <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span> </p>\n<p>e.g.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">answer</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"ow\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kr\">then</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">Stdin</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">line</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">else</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"kt\">Task</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">succeed</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"something\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 440362719,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1716483212
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm curious what others think!</p>",
        "id": 440362737,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1716483219
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Task.ok doesn’t look strange to me here so my preference would be to keep it because it is shorter</p>",
        "id": 440365346,
        "sender_full_name": "Isaac Van Doren",
        "timestamp": 1716484160
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>They look pretty evenly strange to me.</p>",
        "id": 440374385,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1716487994
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But I am used to Ok(...) from all of the rust</p>",
        "id": 440374411,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1716488008
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Succeed makes more sense, but I really like that I don't have to parse Task.ok in my mind. It is so short that just glancing at it I know the meaning of that expression. Task.succeed is just long enaugh to not fall into this category. Besides that, I don't think <code>Task.ok! ...</code> seems strange.</p>",
        "id": 440461518,
        "sender_full_name": "Norbert Hajagos",
        "timestamp": 1716538304
    }
]